ociated with the island of Mull, which claims descent from Gille Eáin na Tuaidh (‘Gillean of the Battleaxe’), who lived in the 13th century."]}]},{"name":"Marion","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a medieval French diminutive form of   Marie  , introduced to Britain in the Middle Ages. In some places it was taken as a pet form of   Margaret   or   Margery .  As a male name, it is an altered form of the Continental male name <i>Marian</i>, a derivative of Latin <i>Marianus</i> (from   Marius  ), but is now rarely, if ever, used. It was the birth name of the American film star  John Wayne  (  1907–79 )."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Marion Maclean was born in 1458, in Scotland as the daughter of John Maclean Of Treshnish. She had at least 1 son with Lachlan MacLean 10th. Chief of Clan MacLean. She died in 1517, at the age of 59."},"et":{"1458–1517":"1458–1517","1456–1513":"1456–1513","1470–1523":"1470–1523","–Male":"Surnud","1458":"1458","1513":"1513","1523":"1523","1456":"1456","1470":"1470","1517":"1517","9 September 1513":"9. september 1513","Duart Castle, Argyll, Scotland":"Duart Castle, Argyll, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","Branxton, Northumberland, England":"Branxton, Northumberland, England"},"fi":{"1458–1517":"1458–1517","1456–1513":"1456–1513","1470–1523":"1470–1523","–Male":"Kuollut","1458":"1458","1513":"1513","1523":"1523","1456":"1456","1470":"1470","1517":"1517","9 September 1513":"9. syyskuuta 1513","Duart Castle, Argyll, Scotland":"Duart Castle, Argyll, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","Branxton, Northumberland, England":"Branxton, Northumberland, England"},"fr":{"1458–1517":"1458–1517","1456–1513":"1456–1513","1470–1523":"1470–1523","–Male":"Décédé","1458":"1458","1513":"1513","1523":"1523","1456":"1456","1470":"1470","1517":"1517","9 September 1513":"9 septembre 1513","Duart Castle, Argyll, Scotland":"Duart Castle, Argyll, Écosse","Scotland":"Écoss